<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisiku seadus </eesti>
<inglise>Employees' Representatives Act </inglise>
<eesti>Vastu v&otilde;etud 16. juunil 1993. a, </eesti>
<inglise>Passed 16 June 1993 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 1993, 40, 595), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT* I 1993, 40, 595), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 25. juunil 1993. a., </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 25 June 1993, </inglise>
<eesti>muudetud j&auml;rgmise seadusega: </eesti>
<inglise>amended by the following Act: </inglise>
<eesti>08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust. 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144 </eesti>
<inglise>08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse &uuml;lesanne </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus kehtestab t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisiku tegevuse &otilde;iguslikud alused teda volitanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahelistes t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act provides the legal bases for the activities of employees' representatives in labour relations between employees who authorise the representatives and employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Usaldusisik on ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni (edaspidi ettev&otilde;te) t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes on valitud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu liikmete v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingusse mittekuuluvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosoleku poolt t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajaks t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A representative is an employee of an enterprise, agency or other organisation (hereafter enterprise) who is elected by the members of a union of employees or by a general meeting of employees who do not belong to a union of employees to represent the employees in labour relations with the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hing on k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes t&ouml;&ouml;suhetealaste huvide esindamiseks ja kaitseks moodustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hendus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, a union of employees is an association of employees formed to represent and protect the interests of employees in labour relations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldusisiku valimine ja tagasikutsumine </eesti>
<inglise>Election and removal of representative </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Usaldusisik valitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A representative shall be elected: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu liikmete poolt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) by the members of a union of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingusse mittekuuluvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>2) by a general meeting of employees who do not belong to a union of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Igal t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingul ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingusse mittekuuluvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosolekul on &otilde;igus vajadusel valida enam kui &uuml;ks usaldusisik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) All unions of employees and general meetings of employees who do no belong to a union of employees have the right to elect more than one representative if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>Enama kui &uuml;he usaldusisiku valimisel lepitakse usaldusisikute arv t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga kokku. </eesti>
<inglise>If more than one representative is to be elected, the number of representatives shall be agreed upon with the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust. 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Usaldusisiku valimise kord ja volituste kestus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu p&otilde;hikirja alusel v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosoleku poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for election of a representative and his or her term of authority shall be determined on the basis of the statutes of the union of employees or by the general meeting of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valitud usaldusisikust informeeritakse kirjalikult t&ouml;&ouml;andjat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The employer shall be notified of the representative elected in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Usaldusisiku ennet&auml;htaegne tagasikutsumine toimub samas korras kui tema valimine. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The procedure for premature removal of a representative shall be the same as the procedure for election. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldusisiku volitajad </eesti>
<inglise>Persons authorising representative </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu usaldusisik esindab &uuml;hingu liikmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A representative of a union of employees represents the members of the union. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingusse mittekuuluvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosolekul valitud usaldusisik esindab t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingusse mittekuuluvaid t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A representative elected by a general meeting of employees who do not belong to a union of employees represents the employees who do not belong to a union. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Usaldusisik v&otilde;ib esindada sama-aegselt erinevate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingute liikmeid ja &uuml;hingutesse mittekuuluvaid t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid &uuml;ldkoosoleku poolt antud volituse ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingute vastavate otsuste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A representative may simultaneously represent the members of different unions of employees and employees who do not belong to a union of employees on the basis of authorisation granted by the general meeting and corresponding decisions made by the unions of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Erinevate volitajatega usaldusisikud v&otilde;ivad ettev&otilde;ttes moodustada oma t&ouml;&ouml; koordineerimiseks &uuml;hiskomisjoni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Representatives authorised by different persons may form a joint committee in an enterprise to co-ordinate their work. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Uuml;hes ettev&otilde;ttes mitme usaldusisiku valimise korral v&otilde;ivad t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hing (&uuml;hingud) ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosolek valida &uuml;hise otsuse alusel usaldusisikute hulgast peausaldusisiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If several representatives are elected in an enterprise, the union (unions) of employees and the general meeting of employees may, by a joint decision, elect a chief representative from among the representatives. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldusisiku kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of representative </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldusisik on teda volitanute nimel kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>On behalf of the persons who authorised him or her, a representative is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esindama t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga; </eesti>
<inglise>1) represent employees in labour relations with the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;lgima kollektiivi ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimuste ning t&ouml;&ouml;seaduste t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) monitor compliance with the terms of collective agreements, employment contracts and labour laws; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hoidma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate poolt t&ouml;&ouml;rahu kollektiivlepingu kehtivuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) observe the obligation of the employees to refrain from striking during the term of a collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vahendama t&ouml;&ouml;vaidluse osapooli; </eesti>
<inglise>4) mediate between the parties to labour disputes; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vahendama tema k&auml;sutuses olevat t&ouml;&ouml;suhetealast teavet t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajaile, nende &uuml;hingutele ja liitudele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) communicate information concerning labour relations known to him or her to the employer or the employer's representative and to employees, their unions and federations; </inglise>
<eesti>6) hoidma talle teatavaks saanud tootmis-, &auml;ri- v&otilde;i ametisaladusi. </eesti>
<inglise>6) maintain any production, business or professional secrets which become known to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldusisiku &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of representative </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Usaldusisikul on teda volitanute nimel &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On behalf of the persons who authorised him or her, a representative has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tutvuda takistamatult t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ja -korraldusega k&otilde;igis t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohtades; </eesti>
<inglise>1) examine freely the working conditions and the organisation of work at all workstations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) saada t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt oma volituste t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) receive information from the employer necessary for exercising the representative's authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) peatada t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine koondamise t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse (RT 1992, 15/16, 241) &sect; 89 tingimustel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) suspend the termination of employment contracts due to a lay-off of employees under the conditions provided for in &sect; 89 of the Employment Contracts Act (RT* 1992, 15/16, 241); </inglise>
<eesti>4) saada t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt teavet t&ouml;&ouml;suhetest tulenevate vaidlusk&uuml;simuste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) receive information from the employer on points of dispute arising from labour relations; </inglise>
<eesti>5) levitada takistamatult t&ouml;&ouml;alast ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid esindava &uuml;hingu tegevust k&auml;sitlevat teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>5) disseminate freely information pertaining to work and the activities of the union of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kasutada kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kuuluvaid t&ouml;&ouml;ruume, side-, paljundus- ja transpordivahendeid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) use, upon agreement with the employer, the premises, telecommunications systems, photocopying facilities and means of transportation of the employer, for the performance of the representative's duties; </inglise>
<eesti>7) informeerida ettev&otilde;tte omanikku, valitsusasutusi, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hinguid ja liite t&ouml;&ouml;seaduste, kollektiivi ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingute ning muude t&ouml;&ouml;alaste kokkulepete rikkumistest t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>7) notify the owner of the enterprise, government agencies, unions and federations of employees of violations of labour laws, collective agreements, employment contracts or other agreements pertaining to work committed by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Peausaldusisikul on &otilde;igus korraldada kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga t&ouml;&ouml; ajal usaldusisikute t&ouml;&ouml;n&otilde;upidamisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A chief representative has the right upon agreement with the employer to arrange meetings with the representatives during working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldusisiku t&ouml;&ouml;suhted </eesti>
<inglise>Employment relationship of representative </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Usaldusisikuks valitud t&ouml;&ouml;taja j&auml;&auml;b t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga t&ouml;&ouml;suhetesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee who is elected as a representative shall remain in an employment relationship with the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Usaldusisiku &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;taja kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga t&ouml;&ouml;v&auml;lisel ajal, p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml; ajal v&otilde;i p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;na (kogu t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala kestel). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The employee shall, upon agreement with the employer, perform the tasks of a representative outside of working time, during working time or as a principal job (throughout the working week). </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;v&auml;lisel v&otilde;i p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml; ajal usaldusisiku &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise tingimused ja kord lepitakse usaldusisiku ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel kokku. </eesti>
<inglise>The conditions and procedure for performance of the tasks of a representative outside of working time or during working time shall be agreed upon by the representative and the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust. 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on usaldusisiku n&otilde;udmisel kohustatud tagama usaldusisikule v&otilde;imaluse oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml; ajal: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At the request of a representative, an employer is required to allow the representative to perform his or her duties during working time: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 5 kuni 100 t&ouml;&ouml;taja esindamise puhul v&auml;hemalt 4 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if the representative represents 5 to 100 employees - a minimum of 4 hours per week; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 101 kuni 300 t&ouml;&ouml;taja esindamise puhul v&auml;hemalt 8 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the representative represents 101 to 300 employees - a minimum of 8 hours per week; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 301 kuni 500 t&ouml;&ouml;taja esindamise puhul v&auml;hemalt 16 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if the representative represents 301 to 500 employees - minimum 16 hours per week; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;le 500 t&ouml;&ouml;taja esindamise puhul kogu t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala kestel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) if the representative represents more than 500 employees - throughout the working week. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust. 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kokkuleppe korral v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;andja tagada usaldusisikule v&otilde;imaluse oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml; ajal kogu t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala kestel ka siis, kui ta esindab alla 500 t&ouml;&ouml;tajat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon agreement, an employer may allow a representative to perform his or her duties during working time throughout the working week even if the representative represents less than 500 employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust. 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Usaldusisiku &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itva t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;leping peatub t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse &sect; 55 kohaselt usaldusisiku &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The employment contract of an employee who performs the duties of a representative is suspended pursuant to &sect; 55 of the Employment Contracts Act for the period he or she performs the duties of a representative. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatised usaldusisikule </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees to representative </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Usaldusisiku &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise aja eest s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt keskmine palk ning t&ouml;&ouml;seaduste, kollektiivi ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud soodustused ja tagatised. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee shall continue to receive from the employer the employee's average wages and any benefits and guarantees provided by labour laws, a collective agreement or employment contract throughout the period the employee performs the duties of a representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust. 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Usaldusisikule laienevad k&otilde;ik seadustes v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingutes s&auml;testatud tagatised, mis on t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ette n&auml;htud ajaks, mil ta esindab t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Guarantees to employees provided by laws or collective agreements shall extend to representatives during the period of time they represent employees. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of disputes </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse rakendamisel tekkivad vaidlused lahendatakse kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamise seaduses (RT I 1993, 26, 442) s&auml;testatud korras v&otilde;i kohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>Disputes arising upon implementation of this Act are resolved pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Collective Labour Dispute Resolution Act (RT I 1993, 26, 442) or in court. * RT = Riigi Teataja = State Gazette </inglise>
